ZH: 他总是独断专行，不听取别人的意见。
EN: He always acts arbitrarily and ignores others' opinions.

ZH: 她在公司里一向独断专行，很少和同事合作。
EN: She always acts independently in the company and rarely cooperates with colleagues.

ZH: 这个领导独断专行，把决定权都握在手里。
EN: This leader acts arbitrarily and keeps all decision-making power to himself.

ZH: 他在这个项目中表现出独断专行的特点，导致团队成员感到不满。
EN: He displayed characteristics of acting arbitrarily in this project, leading to dissatisfaction among team members.

ZH: 即使遭到反对声音，他也一意孤行，独断专行。
EN: Even in face of opposition, he insists on acting according to his own will, ignoring others' opinions.

ZH: 这位总经理的独断专行给公司带来了很多负面影响。
EN: The general manager's arbitrary behavior has brought many negative impacts to the company.

ZH: 他的独断专行让员工们无法理解他的决策。
EN: His arbitrary behavior makes it hard for the employees to understand his decisions.

ZH: 这个老板总是独断专行，不考虑别人的感受。
EN: This boss always acts arbitrarily without considering others' feelings.

ZH: 委员会的决策应该是集体讨论的，而不是一个人独断专行。
EN: The committee's decision-making should be based on collective discussion, not on one person acting arbitrarily.

ZH: 她的独断专行使得整个团队失去了合作的积极性。
EN: Her arbitrary behavior has caused the whole team to lose motivation for cooperation.

ZH: 他的独断专行给公司的形象造成了很大损失。
EN: His arbitrary behavior has caused a great deal of damage to the company's image.

